article.headline: Pacific 79, CS Bakersfield 46
article.story: STOCKTON, Calif. -- Allen Huddleston scored a career-high 18 points to lead Pacific to a 79-46 victory over Cal State Bakersfield on Tuesday night. Sam Willard added 15 points and a career-high 18 rebounds for the Tigers (10-7), who shot 55.4 percent from the field and never trailed. Willard, who had 12 rebounds at halftime, recorded his 12th double-double of the season. He entered the game eighth in the nation in rebounding (10.9 per game). Nyika Williams scored 12 points, Demetrece Young had 10 points and five assists and Pat Eveland scored 10 for the Tigers. Alex Johnson led Bakersfield (8-8) with nine points. The Roadrunners shot 31.7 percent from the field and made just 42.9 percent of their free throws. Huddleston scored 10 consecutive points -- including back-to-back 3-pointers -- as Pacific built a 20-10 lead midway through the first half. Bakersfield never got closer than six points after that.
